This is a file containing documentation on how to download React and test the dashboard.

For starters, we'll need to download React onto our terminal. 

Next we'll need to run the 3 following commands: 
command: node -v 
command: npm -v 
command: npm create vite@latest my-react-app -- --template react **

When this download reaches completion it should ask what you would like to download. 

Click "Typescript + React" 

**We will not use this template. This is just to make sure React is on your machine 

Assuming that you've cloned the repository: type ' cd Capstone-Project-Real-Time-Multi-Robot-Data-Dashboard/src '.

Within this folder (which should contain the frontend files), use 
command: npm install 
to download the dependencies for React. 

Once everything is downloaded, run 
command: npm run dev
to run the dashabord! 

